    "narrative": "LawDog looks to exploit a series of favorable matchups today, with **Lawrence Butler** standing out as our highest-projected asset (74.61). Facing Martin, **Butler** benefits from a massive 17% boost in SP skill projection and a hitter-friendly environment, making him a must-start despite his lower spot in the lineup. Following closely is **Will Smith** (72.25), who draws a juicy matchup against Sugano; the combination of a high-value #3 lineup slot and a significant park factor boost makes him the anchor of our battery. We are also leaning heavily into our exposure against Littell, deploying **Luis Arraez** (68.47), **Matt Chapman** (67.92), and **Jung Hoo Lee** (63.47). Each of these hitters sees a substantial bump from the expected efficiency of this matchup, capitalizing on the high xERA of the opposing starter.\n\nWhile the metrics favor these starts, we must remain cautious with **Cal Raleigh**, whose score of 46.16 reflects the severe risk of facing an elite arm like deGrom. His raw projection is suppressed by a 16% SP skill penalty, leaving him in marginal territory; he stays in the lineup only due to the scarcity of high-impact catchers. On the bench, **Drew Gilbert** was the closest call, posting a respectable 51.68. The decision to bench him in favor of our current outfield alignment came down to the opportunity cost of his #9 batting order position, which dragged down his otherwise solid platoon-advantage metrics. We are proceeding with this lineup to maximize our 5x5 potential, specifically looking for **Gleyber Torres** and **Daulton Varsho** to provide the necessary speed and power contributions, keeping a close eye on the late-afternoon weather reports which could impact the high-ceiling plays like **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**.",
